      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS BLACK DIAMOND (5) resumed over 1200m and led throughout, scoring by 1.3 lengths. She's a strong second-up performer and has a 1.5kg claim today. Draws well and is expected to take some stopping again. RUNAWAY TYCOON (3) resumes after 71 days and has switched from a Brisbane yard. Has been racing in better company and is proven fresh. Has good speed, and Todd's engagement suggests he's ready to go. POLARISING (6) was a big winner this grade and trip but has been plain the two since. Comes back in grade off the latest and has a handy 3kg claim. Can't be ruled out. MIAMI VICE (2) led and turned in a nice effort to score two runs ago at this track. Couldn't follow that up last time in better class, when he settled off the pace. Expect a better run this time.",
